            <h3>Find a Home</h3>
            <hr style=" border-color:black; border-width:medium" />
            <p>
                Having a shelter is like having secuity, privacy and also protection from various calamities. Refugees when they come to Australia they are
                unaware as to where they can get help regarding housing.<br />
                <br />
                Mentioned below are some organisations that support refugees to help settle better.<br />

                <b>Salvation Army</b><br />
                Its and international Christian Movement and they have involved themselves in national issues. Their belief lies in bringing hope to people experiencing hardships or any injustice.
                Get help with respect to home here,
                <a target="_blank" href="https://www.salvationarmy.org.au/locations/victoria/salvation-army-housing/find-us/sah-victoria/">Army Housing Victoria</a><br />

                Know more about housing support services offered by salvation army here,
                <a target="_blank" href="https://www.salvationarmy.org.au/need-help/housing-and-homelessness-support/">Salvation Army</a><br /><br />

                <b>Life without Barriers</b><br />
                This organisation offers various facilities in addition to finding a house. They help people to life to the fullest. Get help regarding housing support here,
                <a target="_blank" href="https://www.lwb.org.au/find-a-service/refugees-and-asylum-seekers/">Life without barriers</a><br /><br />

                <b>AMES Australia</b><br />
                Ames helps in providing various types of accommodation needs to refugees when they arrive in Australia as per their needs. Find more about accommodation here,
                <a target="_blank" href="https://www.ames.net.au/settle-in-aus/accommodation-services">AMES Australia</a><br /><br />

                <b>Migrant Information Centre (MIC)</b><br />
                The organisation assists newly arrived refugees to secure suitable housing facility. MIC has received funding from the Consumers Affairs Victoria and has undertaken the project ‘Migrant and Refugee Rental Housing Assistance’
                <a target="_blank" href="http://miceastmelb.com.au/our-services/housing/">Migrant Information Centre</a><br /><br />

                One can find homes using commercial websites as well:<br />
                <a target="_blank" href="https://www.gumtree.com.au/s-property-for-rent/melbourne/c18364l3001317"><b>Gumtree Australia</b></a><br />
                <a target="_blank" href="https://flatmates.com.au/"><b>Flatmates Australia</b></a><br /><br />
            </p>
