        <h3>Shop budget stuff</h3>
        <hr style=" border-color:black; border-width:medium" />
        <br />
        <p>
            When refugees arrive, they are not quite sure as to from where they can buy groceries and electronics. There are different places in Victoria,
            to go shopping. Mentioned below are some of the places<br /><br />

            <b>Where to buy Groceries:</b><br /><br />

            <b>Foodbank</b><br />
            This is an ASRC free grocery store in Footscray centre that provides essentials to over 800 refugees and asylum seekers.<br />
            <a target="_blank" href="https://www.asrc.org.au/our-work/foodandmaterialsupport/">ASRC Foodbank</a><br /><br />

            <b>Rise Refugees</b><br />
            The Rise foodbank has taken an initiative to address the basic needs of refugees and asylum seekers. They provide access to free dry fruits, fruits and vegetables.<br />
            Rise operates only on Thursday 9am – 5pm and on Saturday 10:30am to 1pm.<br />
            <a target="_blank" href="http://riserefugee.org/">RISE Refugee</a><br /><br />

            <b>Collingwood Cottage Food bank</b><br />
            The organisation aims to provide food products to those in need only on Fridays. One must register themselves at 9am, take a token number and then collect the parcel after 12pm.<br />
            <a target="_blank" href="https://olsc.org.au/cottage.html">Collingwood Cottage Food bank</a><br /><br />

            Apart from these there are other commercial shops which could be used：<br />
            <a target="_blank" href="https://www.aldi.com.au/en/groceries/">Aldi Australia</a><br />
            <a target="_blank" href="https://shop.coles.com.au/a/a-national/home">Coles Australia</a><br /><br />

            <b>Budget Electronics</b><br />
            Find and shop best deals and bargains on electronics and other stuff. <br />
            <a target="_blank" href="https://www.ozbargain.com.au/">Ozbargain Australia</a><br /><br />

            City of Melbourne. Community Food Guide. Retrieved from <a target="_blank" href="https://www.melbourne.vic.gov.au/SiteCollectionDocuments/community-food-guide.pdf">https://www.melbourne.vic.gov.au/SiteCollectionDocuments/community-food-guide.pdf</a>

        </p>
