        <h3>Getting around</h3>
        <hr style=" border-color:black; border-width:medium" />
        <br />
        <p>
            To travel around Victoria, you can do so by using the public transport. One can download the <b>
                PTV
                application
            </b> in their mobile phones and check timings of trains, buses and trams. You would need to
            purchase Myki card, which allows you to travel and use public transport.<br /><br />

            <b>Where to purchase Myki card and top-up?</b><br />
            There are several places from where one could buy Myki card. You can top-up the card in any metro station
            Or online.<br />
            <a target="_blank" href="https://www.ptv.vic.gov.au/tickets/myki/buy-a-myki-and-top-up/where-to-buy-and-top-up/">Buy and Top-up your Myki</a><br /><br />

            You can plan your journey with the help of Journey Planner, feature of PTV application. Learn how to use application here：
            <a target="_blank" href="https://www.ptv.vic.gov.au/footer/about-ptv/digital-tools-and-updates/mobile-apps/how-to-use-the-ptv-app/">Public Transport Victoria (PTV)</a><br /><br />

            Students with refugee status can apply for a concession card. Know more：
            <a target="_blank" href="https://www.ptv.vic.gov.au/tickets/myki/concessions-and-free-travel/children-and-students/tertiary-students/">Apply for a Concession Myki Card</a><br /><br />
        </p>
